explanation: This solution uses dynamic programming to keep track of the number of people who know the secret at each day. The state dp[i] represents the number of people who know the secret at day i. The transition from day j to day i is done by adding the number of people who know the secret at day j to the number of people who know the secret at day i. The result is taken modulo 10^9 + 7 to avoid overflow.

